<section class="pt-faq-hero">
  <div class="pt-faq-hero__content">
    <p class="pt-faq-eye">Got questions</p>
    <h1 class="pt-faq-hero__h1">Everything you need<br><em>to know.</em></h1>
    <p class="pt-faq-hero__sub">If something isn't covered here, drop us a message and we'll get back to you within 24 hours.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="pt-faq-body">
  <div class="pt-faq-inner">

    <!-- FABRIC & QUALITY -->
    <div class="pt-faq-group">
      <p class="pt-faq-group__label">Fabric & Quality</p>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Why is Plain Thread different from other oversized t-shirts?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>Most oversized t-shirts are made to follow trends.</p>
          <p>We made ours to become your everyday favourite.</p>
          <p>From premium combed cotton to a relaxed oversized fit and clean stitching, every detail is chosen for comfort, durability, and simplicity.</p>
          <p>No flashy graphics. No shortcuts. Just a well-made t-shirt you'll enjoy wearing again and again.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Why this t-shirt priced at ₹899?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>A good t-shirt is something you'll wear hundreds of times.</p>
          <p>That's why we chose better fabric, better stitching, and better finishing instead of cutting costs.</p>
          <p>Our premium combed cotton feels softer, lasts longer, and keeps its shape much better than thinner everyday t-shirts.</p>
          <p>You may pay a little more today, but you'll enjoy it for much longer.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Will the tee shrink after washing?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>No.Every Plain Thread t-shirt is pre-shrunk before stitching, so the fit stays almost the same after washing.</p>
          <p>Just wash it in cold water, turn it inside out, and avoid high-heat drying to keep it looking its best.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Will the colour fade?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>Like any good cotton t-shirt, the colour naturally softens over time—but it won't fade quickly with proper care.</p>
          <p>Wash it inside out with cold water, use a mild detergent, and dry it in the shade to keep the colour looking fresh for longer.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- FIT & SIZING -->
    <div class="pt-faq-group">
      <p class="pt-faq-group__label">Fit & Sizing</p>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How does the fit run? Should I size up or down?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>The tee is intentionally oversized. If you want the full drop-shoulder drape as designed, go true to size. If you prefer a more controlled oversized look, size down one.</p>
          <p>The best reference is our <a href="/pages/size-guide" class="pt-faq-link">size guide</a> — it has flat garment measurements so you can compare against a tee you already own. That's the most reliable way to get it right.</p>
          <p>Still unsure, message us—we're always happy to help you choose the right size.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What does "drop shoulder" mean and will it suit me?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>A drop shoulder means the shoulder seam sits slightly lower than a regular t-shirt, giving it a relaxed oversized look.</p>
          <p>It's one of the details that makes the t-shirt feel comfortable while creating a clean, modern silhouette.</p>
          <p>If you've never worn oversized before, don't worry—it suits most body types surprisingly well.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- SHIPPING -->
    <div class="pt-faq-group">
      <p class="pt-faq-group__label">Shipping & Delivery</p>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>How long does delivery take?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>Orders are processed within 1–2 business days. Delivery within Delhi NCR typically takes 2–4 business days. For other cities across India, expect 4–7 business days depending on your location.</p>
          <p>You'll receive a tracking link via SMS and email once your order is dispatched.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Do you offer free shipping?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>Yes — free shipping on all orders above ₹1499.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>Is Cash on Delivery (COD) available?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>Yes, COD is available across most pin codes in India. You can select it at checkout. Please note that COD orders may take an additional 1–2 days to process compared to prepaid orders.</p>
          <p>We recommend prepaid orders for faster dispatch and priority processing.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- RETURNS -->
    <div class="pt-faq-group">
      <p class="pt-faq-group__label">Returns & Exchanges</p>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What is your return and exchange policy?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>If the size isn't right, don't worry—we offer easy size exchanges within 7 days of delivery.</p>
          <p>The t-shirt should be unused, unwashed, and returned with all original tags.</p>
          <p>We don't accept returns for change of mind, but we do take quality issues very seriously. Full details are on our <a href="/pages/shipping-returns" class="pt-faq-link">shipping & returns</a> page.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="pt-faq-item">
        <button class="pt-faq-q" aria-expanded="false">
          <span>What if I receive a damaged or wrong item?</span>
          <span class="pt-faq-icon">+</span>
        </button>
        <div class="pt-faq-a">
          <p>That's on us. Email us at <a href="mailto:support@plainthread.in" class="pt-faq-link">support@plainthread.in</a> with your order number and a photo of the issue within 72 hours of delivery. We'll arrange a replacement or full refund immediately — no questions asked.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="pt-faq-cta">
      <h2 class="pt-faq-cta__title">Still have a question?</h2>
      <p class="pt-faq-cta__sub">We reply within 24 hours on all days.</p>
      <div class="pt-faq-cta__btns">
        <a href="mailto:support@plainthread.in" class="pt-faq-cta__btn-p">Email us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
.pt-faq-hero{
  background:#F7F5EF;
  min-height:280px;
  display:flex;
  align-items:flex-end;
  padding:60px 48px;
  border-bottom:1px solid rgba(18,18,18,0.12);
  position:relative;
  overflow:hidden;
}
.pt-faq-hero::before{
  content:'';position:absolute;inset:0;
  background-image:
    repeating-linear-gradient(0deg,transparent,transparent 48px,rgba(18,18,18,0.03) 48px,rgba(18,18,18,0.03) 49px),
    repeating-linear-gradient(90deg,transparent,transparent 48px,rgba(18,18,18,0.03) 48px,rgba(18,18,18,0.03) 49px);
}
.pt-faq-hero__content{position:relative;z-index:1;max-width:620px}
.pt-faq-eye{
  font-size:10px;letter-spacing:0.22em;text-transform:uppercase;
  color:#121212;margin-bottom:14px;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;
}
.pt-faq-hero__h1{
  font-family:'Playfair Display',serif!important;
  font-size:44px!important;font-weight:400!important;
  color:#121212!important;line-height:1.1!important;
  margin:0 0 16px!important;
}
.pt-faq-hero__h1 em{font-style:italic;color:#121212}
.pt-faq-hero__sub{
  font-size:13px;color:#121212;
  font-weight:300;line-height:1.7;
  font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;max-width:480px;
}
.pt-faq-body{background:#F7F5EF;padding:64px 48px}
.pt-faq-inner{max-width:760px;margin:0 auto}
.pt-faq-group{margin-bottom:52px}
.pt-faq-group__label{
  font-size:10px;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;
  color:#121212;margin-bottom:20px;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;
  padding-bottom:12px;border-bottom:1px solid rgba(18,18,18,0.15);
}
.pt-faq-item{
  border-bottom:1px solid rgba(18,18,18,0.08);
}
.pt-faq-q{
  width:100%;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;
  align-items:center;gap:16px;
  padding:20px 0;
  background:transparent;border:none;cursor:pointer;
  text-align:left;
  font-size:14px;color:#121212;font-weight:400;
  font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;
  transition:color 0.2s;
}
.pt-faq-q:hover{color:#121212}
.pt-faq-q[aria-expanded="true"]{color:#121212}
.pt-faq-icon{
  flex-shrink:0;
  width:24px;height:24px;
  border:1px solid rgba(18,18,18,0.25);
  border-radius:50%;
  display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;
  font-size:14px;color:#121212;font-weight:300;
  transition:transform 0.3s,background 0.2s;
  line-height:1;
}
.pt-faq-q[aria-expanded="true"] .pt-faq-icon{
  transform:rotate(45deg);
  background:rgba(18,18,18,0.1);
}
.pt-faq-a{
  max-height:0;overflow:hidden;
  transition:max-height 0.4s ease,padding 0.3s ease;
  padding:0;
}
.pt-faq-a.open{
  max-height:600px;
  padding-bottom:20px;
}
.pt-faq-a p{
  font-size:13px;color:#121212;line-height:1.85;
  font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;font-weight:300;
  margin-bottom:12px;
}
.pt-faq-a p:last-child{margin-bottom:0}
.pt-faq-link{
  color:#121212;text-decoration:none;
  border-bottom:1px solid rgba(18,18,18,0.3);
  transition:border-color 0.2s;
}
.pt-faq-link:hover{border-color:#121212}
.pt-faq-cta{
  text-align:center;
  padding:56px 0 0;
  border-top:1px solid rgba(18,18,18,0.1);
  margin-top:16px;
}
.pt-faq-cta__title{
  font-family:'Playfair Display',serif!important;
  font-size:32px!important;font-weight:400!important;
  color:#121212!important;margin:0 0 8px!important;
}
.pt-faq-cta__sub{
  font-size:13px;color:#121212;margin-bottom:28px;
  font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;font-weight:300;
}
.pt-faq-cta__btns{display:flex;gap:12px;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap}
.pt-faq-cta__btn-p{
  padding:14px 36px;background:#121212;color:#F7F5EF;
  font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.14em;text-transform:uppercase;
  font-weight:500;border-radius:2px;text-decoration:none;
  font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;transition:background 0.2s;
  display:inline-block;
}
.pt-faq-cta__btn-p:hover{background:#121212}
.pt-faq-cta__btn-s{
  padding:14px 36px;background:transparent;color:#121212;
  font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.14em;text-transform:uppercase;
  border:1px solid rgba(18,18,18,0.2);border-radius:2px;
  text-decoration:none;font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;
  transition:border-color 0.2s,color 0.2s;display:inline-block;
}
.pt-faq-cta__btn-s:hover{border-color:#121212;color:#121212}
@media(max-width:768px){
  .pt-faq-hero{padding:40px 24px;min-height:220px}
  .pt-faq-hero__h1{font-size:32px!important}
  .pt-faq-body{padding:48px 24px}
  .pt-faq-q{font-size:13px}
}
</style>

<script>
document.querySelectorAll('.pt-faq-q').forEach(function(btn){
  btn.addEventListener('click',function(){
    var expanded = this.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';
    var answer = this.nextElementSibling;

    document.querySelectorAll('.pt-faq-q').forEach(function(b){
      b.setAttribute('aria-expanded','false');
      b.nextElementSibling.classList.remove('open');
    });

    if(!expanded){
      this.setAttribute('aria-expanded','true');
      answer.classList.add('open');
    }
  });
});
</script>

